                                        2108,
                                        2379
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Input format: Besides the collected evaluation judgments, we also need to determine the input format for AUTO- J. In early- stage experiments, we attempted to include the scenario criteria as the system message in the input. However, models trained in this manner performed poorly, often simply paraphrasing the scenario criteria. Therefore, we adopt a technique akin to Context Distillation (Bai et al., 2022b) and Ghost Attention (Touvron et al., 2023b), where we omit the inclusion of scenario criteria in the input for the training data, allowing the model to learn them from the output end implicitly. This design significantly enhances the generality of AUTO- J. The final input formats for pairwise comparison and single- response evaluation are in Tab. [17] and Tab. [18] respectively."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
