                                        2106,
                                        2844
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "By integrating data from both pairwise and single- response evaluations, we train our model to seamlessly toggle between diverse evaluation protocols simply by applying the corresponding prompts. To lessen the positional bias (Wang et al., 2023a) in pairwise comparison, we apply a simple data augmentation trick. For each pairwise training sample, we swap the order of two responses in the input and alternate the \"Response 1\" and \"Response 2\" in the evaluation judgment. Since this doubles the pairwise data, we balanced the dataset by duplicating each single- response samples as well."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
